## How to Add Files to GitHub

### Method 1: GitHub Web Interface (Easiest)

1. Go to your repository on github.com
2. Click "Add file" → "Create new file"
3. Type the file path (e.g., `src/App.jsx`)
4. Paste the file contents
5. Click "Commit changes"
6. Repeat for each file

### Method 2: Git Command Line

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/roebling-view-dashboard.git
cd roebling-view-dashboard

# Create folders
mkdir src public

# Create files (paste contents into each)
touch package.json src/App.jsx src/index.js src/index.css public/index.html .gitignore

# After adding content to all files:
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: add dashboard files"
git push
```

